    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you're still framing it like there's a \"correct\" economic view and then these \"side effects.\" if a country manages to revitalize its manufacturing base and create thousands of jobs through tariffs, isn't that a net win regardless of whether prices go up a little bit? why does the consumer cost side always seem to be treated as the definitive way to judge if a policy is successful?",
