      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The focus on consumer cost is a deliberate part of the prevailing economic consensus, which prioritizes free-market efficiency. While job creation is a tangible benefit, the long-term economic damage from higher input costs and reduced innovation due to protectionism is the dominant concern for most economists. Therefore, a policy that trades higher prices for domestic jobs is viewed as a trade-off, not an unqualified success.",
      "source": "target",
